news.title: Average home prices in seven cities at Rs 1.23 crore in H1 FY25: Anarock
news.para: The data reveals that NCR saw the highest average ticket size growth – from approximately Rs 93 lakh in H1 FY24 to over Rs 1.45 crore in H1 FY25. While the value of sold inventory increased by 55% in this period, the total number of units sold declined by 1%.

news.title: Mall operators to see revenue growth of 10-12% in FY25: Report
news.para: High revenue growth last fiscal was driven by full-year contribution of malls launched towards the end of fiscal 2023, supplemented by the half year impact of those that were launched by mid last fiscal; on a like-to-like basis, revenue growth remained stable at ~5%.

news.title: Himachal Pradesh HC orders closure of HPTDC’s 18 loss making prime hotels
news.para: Justice Goel, therefore, directed closure of these 18 hotels in order to ensure that public resources are not wasted by the corporation in the upkeep of these “white elephants” as running of these properties is apparently not financially viable.

news.title: Equity investments in real estate sector to cross $10-11 billion in 2024: Report
news.para: Equity capital inflows touched $8.9 billion between January and September 2024, registering a 46% year-on-year growth.

news.title: Ambuja Cements' stocks dip 17.59%, ACC tanks 14.54% after Gautam Adani's US indictments
news.para: ​​ The stock of the group's flagship firm Adani Enterprises plunged 22.99 per cent, Adani Ports dived 20 per cent, Adani Energy Solutions tanked 20 per cent, Adani Green Energy plummeted 19.53 per cent and Adani Total Gas tumbled 18.14 per cent on the BSE.

news.title: Odisha government to bring in new rehab and resettlement policy for land losers
news.para: ‘Land for land' will be an option besides the existing cash for land compensation. The new policy will replace the 2006 policy.

news.title: Rajasthan government and centre to jointly operate Jaipur metro’s extended lines
news.para: Once the joint venture comes through, state govt will need to cover only 20% of the project's construction cost, said officials. While the Union govt will contribute an additional 20% to the project, the remaining 60% cost will be covered through a soft loan, they added.

news.title: Telangana HC orders land survey to resolve Patelguda villa demolition dispute
news.para: Telangana high court has directed the assistant director of survey and land records of Sangareddy district to survey the land situated at survey numbers 6 and 12 of Patelguda.

news.title: Hyderabad civic body demolishes five-storey building in Gachibowli
news.para: The building, constructed about two years ago, consists of four floors and a penthouse with 12 rooms, all crammed into a compact plot of just 50 square yards.

news.title: Noida: RWAs urge government agencies to act on C&D waste, encroachments
news.para: The residents wrote against dumping C&D waste construction materials in public places, asked for regular cleaning of roads by vacuum suction machines, placing air filters in chimneys of power generation plants and removal of encroachment from roads to streamline vehicular movement.

news.title: Gujarat government places draft jantri rates for public feedback
news.para: Govt sources said the revised annual statement of rates, which reflects jantri rates arrived at through "rationalisation and scientific methods", is likely to take effect from Jan next year.

news.title: NCLT grants approval to capital reduction proposal of Mahindra Homes
news.para: Mahindra Homes had sought confirmation of a ‘special resolution’ passed by its equity shareholders proposing a reduction in the company's issued, subscribed, and paid-up equity share capital.

news.title: Ludhiana smart city works yet to take off, deadline looms
news.para: The tenders issued for the construction of two bridges proposed on Sidhwan Canal and Buddha Dariya are also stuck. The first tender was not successful.

news.title: Punjab and Haryana HC criticizes ED's handling of IREO money laundering probe
news.para: ​​​HC took cognizance of the fact that the accused company's real estate was "conveniently allowed to be disposed of".

news.title: Capitaland Investment to acquire 40% stake in SC Capital Partners Group for $209.31 million
news.para: CapitaLand's 40% stake acquisition in SCCP, a Singapore-based real estate investment manager, will increase its funds under management (FUM) by S$11 billion.

news.title: Myanmar nationals snap up properties in Thailand
news.para: Thai condominium unit sales to Myanmar nationals in the first nine months of 2024 tripled from the same period last year, according to the Real Estate Information Center (REIC), making them the second-largest group of foreign buyers after those from China.

news.title: Gurugram: Raheja Developers moves NCLAT against insolvency proceedings
news.para: On Tuesday, the Principal Bench of the National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT) admitted a plea filed by over 40 of its flat allottees of Sector 109, Gurugram-based projects and directed to initiate a Corporate Insolvency Resolution Process (CIRP).

news.title: Bihar mining department realises Rs 18 lakh fine during raids
news.para: A mines and geology department communiqué said that the raids were conducted to prevent illegal mining, transportation and storage of sand, transportation of stone chips and digging of earth and its transportation for commercial use.

news.title: ED arrests two persons in PMLA case linked to illegal sand mining in Himachal and Uttar Pradesh
news.para: The two persons -- Gian Chand and Sanjay Dhiman -- have been taken into custody under the provisions of the Prevention of Money Laundering Act (PMLA) on Monday, the federal probe agency said in a statement.

news.title: British Land reports higher half-year profit driven by retail park investments
news.para: The British commercial property market is recovering from the post-pandemic freeze, with stabilizing property values and expectations of near-term rate cuts boosting sector optimism.
